    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 200\u00b0C/ 180\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 6</p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) the <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Wash the <strong>leek<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> carefully to remove any grit from between the leaves, then top, tail and slice finely</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/green-pea-risotto-with-seedy-baked-feta/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>sliced leek</strong> and <strong>chopped garlic</strong> and cook for 3-4 min or until beginning to soften</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/green-pea-risotto-with-seedy-baked-feta/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Dissolve the<strong> vegetable stock mix</strong> in 600ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[1.2L]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong></p><p>Once the leek is beginning to soften, add the <strong>arborio rice</strong> and cook for 1 min, stirring to coat the grains in the oil</p><p>Add the <strong>Chinese rice wine</strong>, then slowly add the<strong> vegetable stock</strong> a ladle at a time, stirring continuously for an initial 15 min</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/green-pea-risotto-with-seedy-baked-feta/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, reboil half a kettle</p><p>Tear the <strong>dill </strong>roughly, including the stalks</p><p>Add the <strong>blanched</strong> <strong>peas</strong> to a colander and pour\u00a0<strong>boiled water</strong>\u00a0all over them</p><p>Add <strong>most </strong>of the <strong>peas</strong> (save some for garnish!) to a <strong>food processor</strong> with the <strong>torn</strong> <strong>dill</strong>, <strong>soft cheese</strong> and<strong> </strong>a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> and blitz into a pur\u00e9e \u2013 this is your <strong>pea pur\u00e9e</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/green-pea-risotto-with-seedy-baked-feta/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Cover a baking tray with a thin coat of<strong> olive oil</strong></p><p>Tip: Use some <strong>kitchen paper</strong> to help you spread it evenly!</p><p>Cut the <strong>feta</strong> in half and add it to the oiled tray</p><p>Top the <strong>halved feta</strong> with the <strong>pumpkin seeds </strong>(don't worry if some of them spill over the side!)</p><p>Put the tray in the oven for 10-15 min or until golden \u2013 this is your <strong>seedy baked feta</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/green-pea-risotto-with-seedy-baked-feta/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the rice has been cooking for approx. 15 min, add the <strong>grated Italian hard cheese</strong> to the pan, give everything a good stir and cook for 2-3 min further</p><p>Roll the <strong>lemon<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> with your hand on a hard surface (to release more juice) and cut in half</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/green-pea-risotto-with-seedy-baked-feta/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>pea pur\u00e9e</strong> and the <strong>juice</strong> of <strong>1/2</strong> <span class=\"text-danger\">[1]</span> <strong>lemon</strong> to the pan and give everything a good mix up</p><p>Continue to cook for a final 7-8 min or until all the stock has been absorbed and the rice is cooked \u2013 this is your<strong> green pea risotto</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/green-pea-risotto-with-seedy-baked-feta/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Cut the <strong>remaining lemon</strong> into wedges</p><p>Serve the<strong> green pea risotto</strong> in bowls</p><p>Break the <strong>seedy baked feta</strong> over the top and garnish with the<strong>\u00a0reserved peas </strong>and <strong>lemon wedges</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
